statement.p:
For the function

  f(x)=\frac{\sqrt{x}}{9-x^2}

find the input values which would cause division by zero.

webwork.pg-code:
Context("Inequalities");
Context()->variables->are(x=>'Real',y=>'Real');
$domNumerator=Compute("x >= 0");
$dom=RadioButtons(
["\(x \geqslant 0 \text{ and } x \neq -3\)","\(x \geqslant 0 \text{ and } x \neq 3\)", "\(x \geqslant 0\)"],1,
labels => ["(x >= 0) and (x !0 -3)","(x >= 0) and (x != 3)", "x >= 0"],
displayLabels => 0
);

Context("Inequalities");
Context()->variables->are(x=>'Real',y=>'Real');
$dom1 = Compute("x>=4");
$dom2 = Compute("x<=4");
$dom3 = Compute("x!=7");
$dom4 = Compute("x!= -3 and x!= 3");
